704400f-b.title: Brooklyn: Flushing Avenue - Scott Avenue
704400f-b.text:
(1)
1305-1325 Flushing Avenue, north side, between Scott Avenue
and Seneca Avenue, showing the home of Andrew Samer. For more
data see the New York Sun, February 18, 1939.
1922
Eumene L. Armbruster Collection
(2)
The same, showing the Wyckoff house at the right (No. 1325).
The foreground and to the right of the Wyckoff house, is now
part of Queens County.
May 1923
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
(3)
The same, another view. 99ueens County begins south of
Flushing Avenue, and east of Seneca Avenue.
May 1923
Wugene L. Armbruster Collection
704400f-b.folder: Flushing Avenue & Scott Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
